  "description": "Lohagad is a UNESCO World Heritage site and one of Maharashtra’s most accessible forts. Known for its massive gates, fortified ramparts, and the distinctive 'Vinchu Kata' (scorpion’s tail) extension, Lohagad was historically an important outpost for Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj. The route is well-marked and suited for beginners and families. Views of Pawna Lake, Bhaje Caves, and lush valleys are a highlight—especially during the monsoon.",
